d to locate posts on this issue, as I know that this has been covered before.  I apologize in advance for starting another thread on this topic.<br>
<br>
I am hoping that ours is not the only guild that has discovered that chain does not drop in Kael very often.  I am flailing in the dark trying to find out if we are hunting in the wrong place (generally the arena).  Should we just throw up our hands and go to the PoG?  We aren't quite ready to hit the HoT yet *grin*.<br>
<br>
Any advice would be appreciated.  I am desperate to get some chain for my husband.  We got a pair of arms recently, and lost it due to a MQ mishap.  A guildie who had the quest piece from Thur turned it in first, then my husband was going to turn in the gems.  Turns out that someone had already put 3 gems on the quest npc, so the guy who put the quest piece in got the no-drop piece of armour!  *sigh*  We didn't petition because I assume that Verant has a policy against multi-questing, and wouldn't be interested in our problems.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaidden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aidden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Webmaster</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 12:09:12 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> plenty of chain drops both in Arena and the Tormax Arch...<br>
Keep at it..<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 12:41:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> Hmm... heh, next time I do an armor quest I need to remember to turn in the armor piece first and then the three gems... might save myself some quest gems, heh. :P<br>
<br>
<br>
FWIW, armor drops in Tormax area are much better than Arena from what I've seen.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uamaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaara</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 1:03:23 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> Actually, what you need to remember to do is to turn in 4 pieces of junk to clear the NPC's &quot;cache.&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 1:23:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> 
You sure it works that way?  I don't think it does.  If a quest piece being handed in on top of another quest piece results in the &quot;destruction&quot; of said piece and previous pieces, then you'd only need to hand in one junk piece.  But I don't think it does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uamaara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaara</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 2:14:59 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> Nope, not sure!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   How can we prevent this from happening again?  I am working off of what I learned when getting SoW boots from Hasten.  I was warned that you had to give him enough junk to clear out his cache, because some unkind people would tend to give him stuff intending to mess up the quest.  We should have thought about this during the Thur armor quest, I admit.  It always pays to be more cynical! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzanoan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanoan </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 3:47:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> The &quot;Armor of Zek&quot;s have quite nice drop rate if I remember correctly. =)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoractherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thorac the Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 3:54:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> Notwen - it absolutely works that way!  We were trying to get a warrior some legs the other day.  He wasn't with us in Kael, so another rogue scooped up the plate legs and met the warrior in Thurg.<br>
<br>
The warrior had the gems - and so needed to turn in last.  The rogue handed in the plate legs - AND GOT A PAIR OF WARRIOR NO DROP LEGS!!!!<br>
<br>
Someone had hosed the quest before-hand and left the NPC with just the gems.  GMs won't assist with MQ issues, so now the rogue has a wonderful pair of legs he can't use...<br>
<br>
4 pieces of trash to clear the cache - words to live by.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usdaasiilgladeborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sdaasiil Gladeborn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 8:12:48 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> 4 pieces of trash doesnt work.<br>
<br>
Try it first on an easier quest please. Don't burn quest gems testing this out.<br>
<br>
The only thing that works for sure is killing/waiting for reset the quest mob.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/01 9:47:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> Um, Thorac?  Duh.  That's just multiquesting, of course it works that way.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is that &quot;stacking&quot; of unmatched quest items on an NPC does not function in the way Amaara suggests.<br>
<br>
