Double talk time: I didn't say that you said to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujannellesilverthorne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jannelle Silverthorne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 12:24:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> What they're saying is that Trash is Trash and doesn't end up in the same pool as quest items turned in.<br>
<br>
NPC's record what quest items they were given, and return the quest reward to the first person who completes a set of quest items. They keep this information until they are reset by death or zone repop. And it doesn't matter if they give more than one quest. The ranger Ivy quest giver doesn't care which order you give the runes and gems in, as long as she gets all of them, you'll get the Ivy back. Handy when you've got multiple Runes of Ivy and don't have someone to identify them for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugalaintreeavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galain Treeavenger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 12:35:11 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> Giving 'trash' won't clear anything.  The NPC holds on to quest items until a set condition is met.  For example, You could give an NPC 3 quest gems, then give him all the junk you had and then turn in the proper armor piece and meet his quest condition and still receive your armor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/01 12:53:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thurgadin Quest Armour-- Chain</span><hr size=1> 
What Galain says is what I was basicly getting at. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3038.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3038.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3038.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3038.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesafehouselaboratory">Laboratory<option value="thesafehousefrm15">The Arena<option value="thesafehousefrm17">Anarchy's Grip<option value="thesafehousefrm19">Dark Age of Camelot<option value="thesafehouseoutsidenorrath">Outside Norrath<option value="thesafehouseranthallgripeswishes">Rant Hall<opti